[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Hi, let\'s take a look at the VSX headphones. These are the Immerse ones, the new planner, and these are the previous version. Both are really good, but how do they compare to other headphones? This is the evolution of my headphones for the past 10 years. It starts with the Bose QC35. I know these'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'headphones are not ideal for mixing, but its noise cancellation was way ahead of the competition at the time, and it was ideal for my 9-to-5 job. By the way, I just got laid off, but that\'s for'

[00:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'another video. Then I moved to open-back headphones. These have been my favorite headphones. I was wearing them all day long when I was working from home all the time. They are a bit harsh in the high frequencies, but I got used to the'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'sound. My mixes got better. Starting using them for a long time, and then a year ago, I decided to level up and go with the Beyerdynamic DT 1990 Pro. And now, here\'s the funny part. I think my'

[00:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'mixing skills actually went down with this. I guess the point here is that knowing your gear in and out is way better than any expensive gear that you still don\'t have. And that\'s when I found the Steven Slate Audio VSX'

[01:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'headphones. By the way, this video\'s not sponsored. I have no affiliation with Steven Slate, and I bought these headphones with my money. On the left, we have the original VSX closed-back headphones. On the right, we have the'

[01:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'new Immerse One, more expensive, more premium, open-back with planar magnetic drivers. These headphones are designed to fix the fundamental flaw in mixing with headphones. What is crosstalk? So,'

[01:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'when you\'re listening to speakers, like in this room, you will hear both speakers at the same time with both ears. That means that with your right ear, you\'re still going to listen to the left speaker, and vice versa. So,'

[01:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'everything is mixed into one phantom image. That could lead to issues when you\'re listening to a song in one speaker, let\'s say a HomePod or a Google thing. And the reason is that there\'s a'

[01:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'lot of frequencies that are interacting with each other when you listen to them both or when you\'re listening mono. Then the only solution would be to have a better room, which I cannot do that, or to have a good room with treatment. The'

[02:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'problem is that this room is really small, so I cannot put a lot of treatment because I won\'t be able to walk into the room. That doesn\'t happen with headphones because each ear just gets one channel.'

[02:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'VSX uses binaural modeling to replicate mixing in world-class studios, in cars, in clubs. So it\'s like you can mix in an expensive studio, but in your'

[02:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'headphones. So it recreates that image in the headphones. So both of these headphones, the biggest selling point is that the software and the hardware are tied together. You even have to enter'

[02:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the serial number of the headphones, so they are properly calibrated. So I had the closed-back for 2 months. They\'ve been really useful for mixing. Before having these, I was always bouncing'

[02:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'songs into my phone to listen in to my car, so I can listening to different environments with HomePod, stuff like that. But with these closed-back headphones, I feel like the process has a better been sped up, and I notice'

[03:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'issues in the mix way sooner. And now we have these new headphones, the Immersion One. These are open-back. They they feel more natural. They feel less claustrophobic, if you ask me. This is a premium product. It\'s more expensive'

[03:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'than the closed-back ones. I think you can tell already by the build quality, by how it looks. I think it looks fantastic. Uh but what\'s important is how they sound. I think the clarity in the low end is amazing. I suppose it\'s'

[03:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'all due the planar magnetic drivers. I never heard anything like this before. The transients also are very sharp. But the craziest thing is the bass, like the the the low end. If you listen to music'

[03:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'with lots of bass and lots of low-end, there\'s a lot of clarity there that I don\'t get with other headphones. To give you an example, when going through the different rooms that you have, you have 24 rooms, I believe. One of the rooms is'

[04:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'called club, and it\'s really useful for low-end stuff, like to clear mud in that area. And that one jumps out the most with these new planar. The low-end is so'

[04:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'clear. So, what I found is that with the closed-backs, I I found that room to be useful to tame crazy low-end spikes or kick tails, stuff like that. But but I never really enjoyed the'

[04:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'simulation itself, like it it was a utility room that that helps you identify those problems in the low-end in your mix. But with the new headphones, I feel like the the club is real.'

[04:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'You feel like you are there in the club. For the sake of comparison, it\'s like like using a virtual reality headset. I think the closed-back works, it simulates the world, it gets the job done, it simulates the room. But with'

[04:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the open-back, it\'s like a wider field of view, like 4K resolution or something like that. You can stay in the room longer because the simulation is better. The bass, the drums, the feeling of'

[05:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'being in a club feels more real. And and I guess that\'s due the planar drives. So, to summarize, these work, they get the job done, you get the simulation,'

[05:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you can work with it to to tame the the mix. With these, this simulation is so good that that you feel there in the club. One of my favorite rooms now is the Mike Dean Studio. I really like how'

[05:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the low-end sounds, and I couldn\'t get the same feeling with these ones. So, that\'s one of the things I feel I feel like these were more like a utility that when I needed to use them, I would put'

[05:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the room. With these, I can I can listen to more references for longer because they feel more natural and more like you\'re actually there. The biggest difference between the two is the'

[05:59] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'weight. The original closed-back headphones, they\'re very light. I The only issue for me is that I struggle with closed-back headphones. Like if I have to wear them for long period of times, I feel like it I like a bit'

[06:11] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'trapped in my own head. I work in a quiet environment, so I don\'t really need the isolation that these provide, which is quite a lot. Like I I\'m very impressed. Like even putting it them here and having to listen to my voice,'

[06:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'like it\'s The isolation is good, basically. I mean, they don\'t have noise canceling, but the the passive cancellation is is there. Right now, I use them a lot to track vocals because'

[06:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'there\'s no leak into the mic, and that\'s because they they really cover your ears and the sound stays in there. For comparison, if you ever used a DT 1990 Pro, and these are the 370 g. They'

[06:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'already feel heavy in my head. Uh the Immersion one weighs even more at 430 g. But the headband, so what I found is that the headband does a really good job'

[07:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'at balancing it all. Like it feel it it distributes the weight better. So far, I\'ve been able to use them for long period of times. The weight is there, but I feel like they did a good job with'

[07:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'these band. One thing that is worth mentioning is that these are very very open. They don\'t reject any room noise. You you can hear everything clearly.'

[07:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Like if I put on now and I\'m speaking, like I can feel a slight difference, but it\'s like very minor. Uh the other thing is they bleed a lot. So if you have people around you, they\'re definitely'

[07:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'going to notice and hear what you\'re listening to. And if you\'re going to use them to sing or something, they\'re going to bleed into the mic. So, these are not meant for that. You should use closed-back or'

[07:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'other headphones for singing. I think these headphones are meant to be used with the software so that you can get better mixes. You have two different ways you can use the software. One is by'

[08:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'using the system-wide audio interface. It\'s basically like a VST that runs on your entire computer. So, that is helpful when you want to listen to music on streaming services like Apple Music'

[08:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'in high quality so that you can get used to the rooms. The other way is to use the VST plugin. So, you put it in your DAW at the very end of the main channel. This is just a plugin so that it\'s meant'

[08:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to be bypassed when you are exporting your song. I believe the software does this automatically, but I just do it myself. Now, my only caveat with these systems is that it adds another layer of complexity on your workflow. For'

[08:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'instance, while I was using it on system-wide, I forgot about it and then I started watching a YouTube video. There was a person talking to an SM7B microphone. I\'m very familiar to how it'

[08:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'sounds and I I thought something was off with that video and then it turns out that I had the software with the room activated and I had to bypass that to to feel like I was listening through'

[09:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'headphones. So, you either get used to feeling like it\'s always coming from speakers in front of you or you\'re always having to go through disabling and enabling the plugin depending on what'

[09:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you are doing at the moment. I mean, it\'s not like the end of the world, but it\'s just another thing you have to think about. The software in itself, like it\'s very stable. I had no issues at all while using it. If you buy these,'

[09:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'I really recommend checking out the manual. It has like an explanation of each room, very specific details that are really useful. Now, here\'s one caveat as well with the hardware itself,'

[09:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'especially with the open back. When you active the room simulations, the software drops the volume considerably. I believe this is to leave headroom for the processing. My interface and Arteria Audiofuse Studio drive them perfectly'

[10:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'fine, but when you active the rooms with the plugin, I have to crank the volume knob close to the maximum sometimes, and it feels kind of wrong. I believe the'

[10:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'low end suffers a little bit from it, but it\'s really difficult to tell. So, I don\'t like listening to headphones at high volume. I think you should be careful and protect your ears. So, to manage this, I bought a dedicated'

[10:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'headphone amp. I run an optical cable from my interface to this dedicated headphone amp. It\'s the Topping DX5 2, and the sound is great, and I have a lot of headroom. This might be a little bit'

[10:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'overkill, so I\'ll put the link in the description to this one and another one that is cheaper that gets the job done. I just prefer to have this one because it had the optical and other features that that are not relevant to this'

[10:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'video. So, do you really need to spend this kind of money on the higher end? I think these are amazing. The low end is I never heard something like this. I never used a subwoofer, so this seems'

[11:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'like the closest thing to a subwoofer in a room and and the big low end and defined low end. So, it\'s amazing. I believe you can still go with the'

[11:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'cheapest one. It\'s still not cheap, but I mean, it\'s cheaper than the other one. And and I believe these are fantastic to getting your mixes right. And personally, I still believe in the'

[11:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'craft of making music from zero from the starting line to the final mix and mastered song. I really love and enjoy the process. I think these headphones will help me a lot in achieve those'

[11:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'goals. Having a good room with good acoustics and treating the treating it and all of that, it\'s not a possibility for most of us. So, this is a good alternative. Well, also honorable'

[12:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'mention to my AirPods. I use them all the time to listen to YouTube video and cook something. Shout out to those. So, yeah. Stay cool and see you on the next one. Bye.'
